                            <comment id="255580" author="spiechurski" created="Mon, 30 Sep 2019 09:57:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello @Minh,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A number of users and vendors (including us Atos/Bull) are expecting to install the current 2.12 LTS on RHEL 7.7 with MOFED (which only 4.7 brings compatibility with RHEL 7.7 kernels).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On top of this, Peter announced last week during the LAD, that 2.12.3 would be released with compatibility of MOFED 4.7.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I think it is needed to have this in b2_12.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You will also need to cherry-pick those dependencies which are not present on b2_12:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;27572b047:&#160;&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12355&quot; title=&quot;Support for linux kernel version 5.0&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12355&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12355&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lnet: Adjust checks for ib_device_ops&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;bbc2cf593:&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12400&quot; title=&quot;Support for linux kernel version 5.2&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12400&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12400&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lnet: Infiniband sg_dma changes for linux 5.1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;46298ffe0b436a8cf1c60aa3d7bde7ae52c78d00:&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12355&quot; title=&quot;Support for linux kernel version 5.0&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12355&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12355&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lnet: ib_fmr_pool_unmap returns void&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="255559" author="shadow" created="Sun, 29 Sep 2019 08:51:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Minh, a zero cost support and just bug fixes for configure checks in patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
